      "comment": "QUEEN OF SEES (2) raced just twice at her maiden campaign, finishing runner-up as a hot favourite on debut before tackling a Vicbred Super Series heat. Has not raced for six months but draws well and looks ready for a successful return after winning two recent trials. JILLIBY RADIANCE (1) kicked off her career with a win a month ago, leading from wider and getting home by 1.1 metres at Maryborough. Has upside and can take advantage of the ace draw. ALDEBARAN MIGUEL (10) was well fancied last start but broke. Had a flat tyre on debut prior so did well for fourth. Worth another chance. ISLAND FRANKIE (8) was well beaten fresh but won here in his only other appearance. Could be a big improver.",
